    load 'deploy/assets'
# load 'config/deploy' # remove this line to skip loading any of the default tasksCap's got built in tasks for Rails migrations: You can run cap deploy:migrate to only run migrations on your server (the one marked with role :db and :primary => true) without a new deploy push too, or you can cap deploy:migrations to deploy+migrations. But this requires you to think about "do I need to run migrations this release?"

